// Hand-maintained: NOT generated by mmtorust.
//
// Rust port of `OMCompiler/Compiler/Util/Autoconf.mo`. Upstream, that file
// is produced at *configure time* by substituting platform facts into
// `Autoconf.mo.in` (Unix) or `Autoconf.mo.omdev.mingw` (Windows/OMDev).
// The Rust port runs no configure step, so this module is hand-written and
// detects the platform with Rust's compile-time `cfg!` instead; `Autoconf`
// is listed in `HANDWRITTEN_TOP_PACKAGES` (mmtorust/src/codegen.rs) to skip
// its codegen.
//
// Values mirror what the two upstream templates produce on each platform:
//
//   * Linux   — the values configure substitutes on a GNU/Linux host
//     (the same ones the previously generated file carried).
//   * Windows — `Autoconf.mo.omdev.mingw` with a current OMDev
//     (`isNewOMDev` / `isNewNewOMDev` both true), i.e. a MinGW
//     toolchain. The link-flag soup is kept verbatim from that file.
//   * macOS   — best-effort: configure substitutes `.dylib` / no
//     `-Wl,-Bstatic`; the ldflags mirror the Linux set minus the
//     GNU-ld-only options. Untested — verify against a configured
//     `Autoconf.mo` before relying on a macOS build.
//
// The constants must stay `const` (not `static`): generated code embeds
// them with `arcstr::literal!(Autoconf::xxx)` and in `const_str::equal!`
// comparisons, both of which require const expressions.

